 can apply for global investment centre if you are aged  or over are a uk resident with a permanent uk residential address have an hsbc current andor savings account you cannot apply for a funds portfolio and isa funds portfolio if youre a nonuk resident including if you are a uk crown servant working overseas accounts cannot be held in joint names and nonpersonal accounts are not permitted if you would like to invest with another person or to make regular contributions rather than investing a lump sum please call   to discuss your options please read the important information below global investment centre has been created for individual investors who want to make lump sum investments themselves you cannot make regular payments or joint applications in to the global investment centre investors should regularly review the funds theyve chosen thats why with global investment centre you can see the current value of your investments and track their performance at a glance once youve applied for the global investment centre you can open a funds portfolio in which to buy sell and hold your investments you can also apply for an isa funds portfolio so you can hold your investments within a taxefficient isa the minimum initial investment is £ for each class of fund shares for each portfolio the minimum additional investment is also £ online trades through the global investment centre are limited to £ if you would like to place a trade of £ or more you may do so by phone – please call us on   find the fund that’s right for you click on a fund provider or tell us what kind of fund you’re looking for and we’ll help you find the fund that fits your criteria fund type all fund types accumulation income sector all sectors asia pacific excluding japan asia pacific including japan china  greater china european smaller companies europe excluding uk europe including uk flexible investment gbp corporate bond gbp high yield gbp strategic bond global global bonds global emerging markets